snippet.textDisplay: @Epicurious can you do a series where subscribers present to you recipes they like, but which feel like they are missing something or could be improved? For example, i have smoked salmon and cream pasta almost every week, but i feel like something's missing to it. My recipe is: some finely chopped garlic goes into the frying pan with some olive oil and the salmon cut to nail sized pieces for a minute or so, after which i put a sufficient portion of cream on top of everything and i let it cook for 15-20 minutes. During this time, the cream first turns liquid, then it drops until it becomes like a rather thick sauce. I then put the pasta inside, stir for 1 minute and plate it, put some black pepper, grate some grana padano into it and it's done. Although it's delicious, I feel however that something could be added to make it better.
snippet.textOriginal: @Epicurious can you do a series where subscribers present to you recipes they like, but which feel like they are missing something or could be improved? For example, i have smoked salmon and cream pasta almost every week, but i feel like something's missing to it. My recipe is: some finely chopped garlic goes into the frying pan with some olive oil and the salmon cut to nail sized pieces for a minute or so, after which i put a sufficient portion of cream on top of everything and i let it cook for 15-20 minutes. During this time, the cream first turns liquid, then it drops until it becomes like a rather thick sauce. I then put the pasta inside, stir for 1 minute and plate it, put some black pepper, grate some grana padano into it and it's done. Although it's delicious, I feel however that something could be added to make it better.
